Vice President Kamala Harris convened civil society and business leaders in Northern Thailand to discuss climate action and environmental activism. She reiterated the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to supporting a sustainable and clean energy future for Thailand and the Mekong sub-region. The Vice President highlighted the intersection of climate crisis with shared priorities such as public health, sustainable livelihoods, and economic growth. Participants discussed environmental protection, youth empowerment, economic development, and innovation in the clean energy sector. The Vice President emphasized the importance of coalition building and announced new funding for clean energy and sustainable economic development in the region.